\DOC mk_disj

\TYPE {mk_disj : term * term -> term}

\SYNOPSIS
Constructs a disjunction.

\DESCRIBE
{mk_disj(`t1`,`t2`)} returns {`t1 \/ t2`}.

\FAILURE
Fails with {mk_disj} if either {t1} or {t2} are not of type {`:bool`}.

\EXAMPLE
{
  # mk_disj(`x = 1`,`y <= 2`);;
  val it : term = `x = 1 \/ y <= 2`
}

\SEEALSO
dest_disj, is_disj, list_mk_disj.

\ENDDOC
